#an represents the nth term
#a represents the first term
#n represents the term number
#d represents the common difference between consecutive terms.

a = int(input("enter 1st term: "))
a2 = int(input("enter 2nd term: "))
n = int(input("enter term number to find: "))
d = (a2 - a)
an = a + (n-1)*d
print("the ",n,"th term of the series is: ",an)

#output
#enter 1st term: 2
#enter 2nd term: 5
#enter term number to find: 4
#the  4 th term of the series is:  11

